com.oceanoptics.highrestiming

Class HighResTimeStamp

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.oceanoptics.highrestiming.HighResTimeStamp

  • public class HighResTimeStamp
extends java.lang.Object
    This builds on the HighResTiming object to encapsulate the nanosecond interval timer with the millisecond system time. While the nanoseconds will not be exactly registered to the milliseconds (there is no way no set the nanosecond zero time to an exact millisecond boundary), this will anchor it for all practical purposes -- absolute time will always be given in milliseconds, and deltas will be given in nanoseconds.
